# Analysis of the Main Target Image

## Count & Layers
- The structure has 3 distinct blocks total
- There are 3 layers:
  - Bottom layer: A green rectangular block (base)
  - Middle layer: An orange cylindrical block
  - Top layer: An orange triangular/pyramidal roof

## Spatial Relationships
- The green rectangular block serves as the base, positioned horizontally
- The orange cylindrical block stands vertically on top of the center of the green base
- The orange triangular/pyramidal roof sits on top of the cylinder, forming a house-like structure

# Required Blocks from the Dictionary

Based on my analysis, I need the following blocks from the dictionary:
1. Green rectangular block in horizontal orientation (Block index 2)
2. Orange cylindrical block in vertical orientation (Block index 5)
3. Orange triangular/pyramidal roof piece (Block index 11)

# Assembly Order

```
{
  Step1: Move block with index 2
  Step2: Move block with index 5
  Step3: Move block with index 11
}
```

This assembly order follows a bottom-to-top approach, starting with the green base, adding the orange cylindrical column, and finishing with the triangular roof to complete the house-like structure.
